<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="503" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,516,975]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">
Colouration and structure as described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Distant, W. L." box="[631,799,516,541]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" pagination="1 - 210" refId="ref4944" refString="Distant, W. L. (1918) Rhynchota Homoptera: Appendix. Heteroptera: Addenda. In: Shipley, A. E. &amp; Marshall, G. A. K. (Eds.), The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Uol. 7. Taylor &amp; Francis, London, pp. i-viii + 1 - 210." type="book chapter" year="1918">Distant (1918)</bibRefCitation>
. Crown of vertex more than 1.5 times as broad between eyes as medially long. Pronotum more than twice as long as crown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,516,975]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,407,588,613]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Seventh sternite longer medially than sixth, lateral angles of posterior margin rounded, posterior margin medially produced with median concavity, lateral margins of concavity smoothly rounded, area adjacent to median projection concave
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,516,975]" box="[199,1292,695,720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,695,720]" pageId="2" pageNumber="503">Measurement.</emphasis>
Female 
<quantity box="[467,552,695,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="6.4">6.4 mm</quantity>
long, head 
<quantity box="[683,783,695,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.64" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="2.64">2.64 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes, 
<quantity box="[992,1092,696,720]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.04" pageId="2" pageNumber="503" unit="mm" value="3.04">3.04 mm</quantity>
across pronotum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
